#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:1
msgid "Related Projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:3
msgid "WebAssembly ecosystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:5
msgid ""
"[emscripten](https://emscripten.org/) is the compiler toolchain for "
"WebAssembly that made Pyodide possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:8
msgid "Notebook environments, IDEs, and REPLs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:10
msgid ""
"[Iodide](https://github.com/iodide-project/iodide) is a notebook-like "
"environment for literate scientific computing and communication for the web. "
"It is no longer actively maintained. Historically, Pyodide started as plugin "
"for iodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:14
msgid ""
"[Starboard notebook](https://github.com/gzuidhof/starboard-notebook) is an "
"in-browser literal notebook runtime that uses Pyodide for Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:16
msgid ""
"[Basthon notebook](https://notebook.basthon.fr/) is a static fork of Jupyter "
"notebook with a Pyodide kernel (currently in French)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:18
msgid ""
"[JupyterLite](https://github.com/jupyterlite/jupyterlite) is a JupyterLab "
"distribution that runs entirely in the browser, based on Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:20
msgid ""
"[PyScript](https://pyscript.net/) is an open source platform for Python in "
"the browser. It defines `<script type=\"py\">` html elements to allow "
"creation of JavaScript-free HTML/CSS/Python web applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:23
msgid ""
"[futurecoder](https://futurecoder.io/) is an interactive Python course "
"running on Pyodide. It includes an [IDE](https://futurecoder.io/course/#ide) "
"with a REPL, debuggers, and automatic installation of any imported packages "
"supported by Pyodide's `micropip`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:28
msgid ""
"[react-py Playground](https://elilambnz.github.io/react-py/playground) uses "
"Pyodide as part of the `react-py` package documentation. Try out code "
"snippets and packages directly in your browser without logging in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:29
msgid ""
"[marimo](https://github.com/marimo-team/marimo) is a reactive notebook that "
"is compatible with Pyodide with an [online editor](https://marimo.app/) that "
"runs entirely in the browser. These notebooks can also run as standalone "
"applications or embedded in blogs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:30
msgid ""
"[quarto-pyodide](https://github.com/coatless-quarto/pyodide) uses Pyodide to "
"create interactive code cells and documents within a variety of [Quarto]"
"(https://quarto.org/) document formats like HTML Documents, RevealJS, Books, "
"and Websites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:34
msgid ""
"[PyCafe](https://py.cafe) lets you host, edit, and share Python apps in your "
"browser with a single click."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:35
msgid ""
"[quarto-live](https://github.com/r-wasm/quarto-live) uses Pyodide to create "
"interactive Python code cells and exercises in [Quarto](https://quarto.org/) "
"documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:37
msgid ""
"[Online Laboratory for Climate Science and Meteorology](https://github.com/"
"climet-eu/lab) is a JupyterLite-based environment that comes with additional "
"packages from the weather and climate community, and patches to support "
"loading and working with large (remote) datasets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:40
msgid ""
"[Cubite](https://cubite.io) is a multi-tenant LMS platform that uses Pyodide "
"for in-browser Python execution in course content via a custom [EditorJS "
"plugin](https://github.com/amirtds/editorjs-code-editor). Read more about "
"[how Cubite uses Pyodide for interactive learning](https://cubite.io/blogs/"
"run-python-in-browser-pyodide-editorjs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:42
msgid "Workarounds for common WASM and browser limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:44
msgid ""
"[pyodide-http](https://github.com/koenvo/pyodide-http) Provides patches for "
"widely used http libraries to make them work in Pyodide environments like "
"JupyterLite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:48
msgid "Dashboards and visualization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:50
msgid ""
"[WebDash](https://github.com/ibdafna/webdash) is a Plotly Dash distribution "
"that runs entirely in the browser, using Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:52
msgid ""
"[Flet](https://flet.dev) is a UI framework for your Pyodide apps based on "
"Flutter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:53
msgid ""
"[stlite](https://github.com/whitphx/stlite) is a serverless version of "
"[Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/) running on Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:54
msgid ""
"[Gradio-Lite](https://www.gradio.app/guides/gradio-lite) is a serverless "
"version of [Gradio](https://www.gradio.app/) running on Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:56
msgid "Other projects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:58
msgid ""
"[wc-code](https://github.com/vanillawc/wc-code) is a library to run "
"JavaScript, Python, and Theme in the browser with inline code blocks. It "
"uses Pyodide to execute Python code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:61
msgid ""
"[SymPy Beta](https://github.com/eagleoflqj/sympy_beta) is a fork of SymPy "
"Gamma. It's an in-browser answer engine with a Pyodide backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:63
msgid ""
"[react-py](https://github.com/elilambnz/react-py) is a library that allows "
"for easy integration of Pyodide in React applications. It provides "
"convenient hooks for running Python code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/related-projects.md:64
msgid ""
"[inseri core](https://wordpress.org/plugins/inseri-core/) is a WordPress "
"plugin that introduces scientific and interactive Gutenberg blocks to "
"facilitate open science. The [Python Code block](https://docs.inseri.swiss/"
"blocks/python/) allows to run Python code in the browser using Pyodide."
msgstr ""
